node.text:
Giving strangers Special Effects Makeovers with @makeuppbyruthie. Which makeover was your favorite?

Usually I don’t show all the rejections that I face in filming my content for you guys, but this time I showed every rejection I encountered to film these two photoshoots. Hope you enjoy seeing that part!

What should we transform a stranger into next?

Strangers are @kennacolee and @acidgumibears 
Behind the scenes by @thevidkid1
Smoke bombs by @smoky.bombs 
Dress by @andrea_leo_couture

node.text:
Street photography in Las Vegas! Which shoot was your favorite?

This is the first of a two-part series from my recent trip to Las Vegas! I had a lot of fun there and hope you guys enjoyed seeing the interesting people I found.

This episode features 3 amazingly talented creators each of which amassed millions of followers within less than a year!

Creator 1: @jakefellman 
Jake is a 3D artist that has amassed 5 million YouTube followers in a matter of half a year using his creativity in short form videos.

Creator 2: @itsdanielmac 
Daniel Mac has grown over 10 million followers by asking one question! He was able to leave his 9 to 5 job to do content creation full time.

Creator 3: @iamtiagz 
Tiagz has an inspirational story where he posted 701 videos that all flopped. His next video went viral and since then his life transformed with over 5 million followers and getting signed by Epic Records.

node.text:
This episode is titled “Jokers” and highlights three cosplayers I was able to find walking around Hollywood Blvd. Which photoshoot was your favorite?

The first video went mega viral on TikTok with nearly 60 million views so I called back Joker and Batman for a follow-up shoot. 

The third video was the first Joker I found and the first time I shot cosplay. It also went very viral on TikTok with almost 40 million views.

Which Joker is your favorite?

Video 1 and 2:
Joker = @agentsofkhaos 
Batman = @lucidluminos 

Video 3:
Joker = @mrjjoker369 

Smoke bombs by @smoky.bombs 
Behind the scenes by @jessbillings_ @jake.ceja

node.text:
We surprised a mom and her husband with a pop-up concert and photoshoot featuring AJ McLean (@aj_mclean) and his new song “Love Song Love”. Happy Mother’s Day!

The couple is @blahblahblah27 & @dopesince1983 

They are big fans of AJ and thought they were just being treated to a picnic dinner that day until AJ McLean himself and I surprised them with this pop-up concert!

Behind the scenes by @jessbillings_

node.title: Surprising fans with Backstreet Boy AJ McLean

node.text:
Me and @makeuppbyruthie turned a complete stranger into a Tim Burton Corpse Bride! Which photo is your favorite? 

After facing a ton of rejections we finally found a stranger willing to do an impromptu special effects makeover. That stranger was @kennacolee who was visiting with family from Oklahoma. 

The makeover and photoshoot took a couple of hours and was done right on Hollywood Blvd. 

👗: @andrea_leo_couture 
💨: @smoky.bombs 
BTS: @thevidkid1 

Do you enjoy this new series? What should we turn a stranger into next?

Me and @makeuppbyruthie gave a stranger a Tim Burton’s Corpse Bride makeover!

After facing a ton of rejections asking strangers to do this makeover, we finally met @kennacolee who was up for it! The makeover and photoshoot took about two hours!

Hope you enjoyed the result. What should we turn a stranger into next to continue this series?

Dress by @andrea_leo_couture

We turned a stranger into the Suicide Squad Joker with @makeuppbyruthie

Swipe to see some crazy 👀 details and the behind the scenes. Which photo was your favorite?

The makeup took about an hour to apply and also finding a stranger that was willing to do this took about an hour as well! Thank you to the brave @acidgumibears for volunteering to do this spontaneous makeover with us!

Shot on a Sony a7r iii with a Sony GM 50mm f1.2 lens! #photography #portraitphotography #joker

node.text:
This is Ted @tedhayes.us, a 70 year old activist, roller-skater and cancer survivor that I met in Venice beach.

When I saw Ted I knew I had to capture some photos of him and after talking to him I found out he is a really kind and interesting person.

Ted told me that he recently beat cancer and is already back on his rollerskates! He told me that he has ambitions of getting social media sponsorships for the health and supplement space. I told him I would see if I could help by mentioning it in my post!

Ted has been an advocate of fixing the homeless crisis in Venice for 36 years. He holds the American flag upside down to signify a state of distress in our country. Ted also runs a website called mattersofblacklives.com. He is truly passionate about bringing change in his local community and the country as well.

node.text:
Shot on the OnePlus 9 Pro @oneplus_usa , which photo is your favorite?

A lot of my followers have asked me for mobile photography tips! I believe that we don’t need expensive gear to be able to take photos that tell a story. I want to encourage people to use whatever gear they have to take the best photos they can! My favorite phrase is: The best camera is the one in your hands. 

#MobileMasterpiece

node.text:
Follow @alexanderthegreat for more videos…

Did these photos tell a love story 😍 Which photo is your favorite?

I met this couple at The Grove and what caught my eye was their matching outfits! Funny enough they didn’t even realize they were matching that day lol.

Another part of this side story was this was the day I invited a follower named Aaron to shadow me during a stranger photoshoot. He experienced my entire process which included walking around for hours before finally picking this couple for the first shoot that day. 

Also, the couple happened to be visiting a bookstore to meet with an agent about their upcoming book called A Child of Magic. Can’t wait for them to update me on that progress as it sounded like an amazing book!

node.text:
Results are on @thevidkid1 … I brought a follower to shadow me yesterday and got him to do a stranger photoshoot! He’s been shooting for only 2 months, check out the photos on his page @thevidkid1 

It felt great to help build up a beginner photographer, I can’t imagine having an experience like this when I was just two months in. Thank you guys for supporting him, he only had 23 followers yesterday morning when I met him.

I plan on doing another shadow session with a follower here in LA and maybe during my next trip to Miami so pay close attention to my stories for those announcements!

Behind the scenes by @jessbillings
